Open APC Sweden - Statistics

This is an example of statistics from the pilot project Open APC Sweden, aiming at gathering data about article processing charges (APC’s) paid by Swedish universities. The statistics cover journal articles published mainly between 2014 and 2 017 from a few pilot contributors. Please see the project wiki for more information about the project and instructions on how to contribute.

Contributing organisations and publishers

These Swedish universities have reported APC costs for their articles so far:

A number of publishers have also supplied Open APC Sweden with data:

Publishers
Springer
Taylor & Francis
Karger
IOP Publishing
Copernicus

This publisher-supplied data leads to publishing costs being reported for a number of Swedish research institutions which not yet have supplied us with data actively.

Dataset

Information on both open access journal articles, open access publication of articles in toll-access journals (‘hybrid’) and articles published within current Swedish Offset deals are provided. You may view the dataset at the project page in GitHub.

Open Access Articles (Total: ‘gold’, ‘hybrid’ and ‘offset’)

At the moment, the dataset contains the following information:

  • Number of articles: 4 585
  • Total expenditure: 8 640 595 €
  • Average fee: 1 885 €
  • Median fee: 2 200 €

Articles in Open Access journals (‘gold OA’)

At the moment, the dataset contains the following information on articles in open access journals:

  • Number of articles: 1 609
  • Total expenditure: 2 097 146 €
  • Average fee: 1 303 €
  • Median fee: 1 325 €
  • Share of articles with no fees: 6.2 %

OA articles in toll-access journals (‘hybrid OA’), Offset articles excluded

In many toll-access journals some of the articles are open access after a fee has been paid. This model is often called ‘hybrid open access’. The dataset covers the following data on hybrid open access articles:

  • Number of articles: 1 047
  • Total expenditure: 2 299 649 €
  • Average fee: 2 196 €
  • Median fee: 2 200 €
  • Share of articles with no fees: 0.38 %

OA articles in offset deals

In offset deals a total number of articles is agreed upon, together with a license fee. The dataset covers the following data on offset deal articles:

  • Publishers with current offset deals: Springer
  • Number of articles: 1 929

Acknowledgement

This project follows the Open APC Initiative to share data on paid APCs. It recognises efforts from JISC and FWF to standardise APC reporting.
